news.title: Ludhiana improvement trust richer by Rs 149 crore after land deal with GST department
news.para: The chairman claimed that now they have at least Rs 200 crores in their kitty and this amount will be spent on the development of city with various works as some are ongoing and some are in pipeline.

news.title: Rajasthan's revenue department to regularise land under JDA
news.para: Replying to the supplementary questions, the minister said there are many conditions related to regularization on restricted lands under List- 4 and this provision will not be applicable to them.

news.title: Nagpur: No permission for Nirmal Nagri to cut 67 trees
news.para: The state transport department had sought permission to fell 1,014 trees for constructing a parking plaza near Mor Bhavan and about 211 trees for a bus depot at Wadi.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to offer tax sops to restore heritage buildings
news.para: ​At the same time, the civic body will take the responsibility of maintaining a section of heritage buildings that are ill maintained due to apathy of owners. In such cases, KMC will attach the maintenance bills to the property tax.

news.title: Over seven lakh eligible people left out of PMAY: Rajasthan's rural development minister
news.para: “Of the 23 lakh eligible people under PMAY-G in the state, names of 7.15 lakh have been left out. In all, 11 letters have been written by the department to the centre urging them to add the names,” he said.

news.title: Circle rate hike planned by Delhi government will adversely impact real estate: Experts
news.para: “Any proposal to hike circle rates in Category A localities - Maharani Bagh, New Friends Colony, Panchsheel Park, Vasant Vihar and Hanuman Road - where the market rates are significantly below circle rates will be very counterproductive,” said Amit Goyal, CEO, India Sotheby’s International Realty.

news.title: Maharashtra's revenue from property registrations to hit new high in FY22: Report
news.para: Within the first 11 months of FY22, the state has earned Rs 5,671 crore from property registrations, which is 63 per cent higher than Rs 3,474 crore in FY21.

news.title: SWAMIH fund to help complete 12,000 flats annually in stalled projects for next 2-3 years
news.para: ​In November 2020, the Centre had announced a Rs 25,000-crore fund, named Special Window for Affordable and Mid-Income Housing (SWAMIH), to help complete over 1,500 stalled housing projects comprising 4.58 lakh housing units across the country.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance board to take call on fundraising on March 9
news.para: ​A meeting of the Board of Directors of PNB Housing Finance Limited is scheduled to be held on March 9 to consider fund raising options by issue of equity shares through appropriate methods (including rights issue), subject to requisite approvals, the company said in a regulatory filing on Friday.

news.title: Maharashtra: 1% metro cess on property buys from next month
news.para: Property buyers currently pay 6% stamp duty in these three cities. The 1% metro cess would be a transport surcharge. It is intended to be used for funding transport infrastructure projects like Metro, bridges and flyovers.

news.title: Steel prices jump up to Rs 5,000 per tonne as supply chains hit amid Russia-Ukraine conflict
news.para: After the price revision, a tonne of HRC will cost around Rs 66,000, while the buyers will get TMT bars for about Rs 65,000 per tonne, the sources said on Friday.

news.title: 'Colluded with builder', SBI officials booked in Ghaziabad
news.para: The housing project — initially publicised in the name of Red Apple Residency — was launched in 2012, but it has still not seen the light of the day.

news.title: Country Garden & Midea Real Estate secure $3.3 billion M&A funding
news.para: In separate statements late on Thursday, Country Garden said it had signed a deal for 15 billion yuan ($2.37 billion) in M&A facilities with China Merchants, while Midea said it had agreed a deal with the same lender for 6 billion yuan in M&A funds.

news.title: Activists remind Navi Mumbai civic body about row houses' encroachment
news.para: Mahendra Sapre, he stated: ``We have again conducted a survey of the said six-row houses, and soon appropriate action will be taken."

news.title: PFC ties up with Faridabad civic body to install LED streetlights
news.para: ​According to the memorandum of understanding (MoU), PFC will provide financial assistance of Rs 3.56 crore to the MCF for supply, installation and commissioning of 4,324 LED street light systems in 21 villages of Faridabad, Haryana.
